HEADWORD: Rabdology
<hw>Rab*dol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(r⟦acr⟧b*d⟦ocr⟧l"⟦osl⟧*j⟦ycr⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>"ra`bdos</grk> rod, stick +
<ets>-logy</ets>: cf. F. <ets>rabdologie</ets>.]</ety> <def>The method
or art of performing arithmetical operations by means of Napier's bones.
See <er>Napier's bones</er>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>rhabdology</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

